<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-47-0076 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author first reviews Canada's petroleum reserves, then summarizesthe problem facing Canada regarding dwindling supplies of conventionallight and medium crude oils and briefly describes Canada's refining capability.With that background, he attempts to analyze the problems that face heavyoil producers in attempting to market their product and propose a potentialsolution to these problems as illustrated by Husky Oil's approach - theconstruction of a heavy oil upgrader. He closes by sharing his viewson the future of heavy oil development and the policy issues facing ourgovernments.</TEXT></DOC>